  <text>
    <body>
      <pb n="1" />
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <date when="1873-06-03">June 3rd 3</date>
          </dateline>
          <salute>Dear <persName ref="#stillca">Katie</persName></salute>
        </opener>
        <p>
          Your letter of the 30th inst<lb/> with the money order for twenty<lb/> 75/100 dollars to pay up your back <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd">orders</unclear><lb/> for the U.G.R.R. came duly to hand yesterday and let me assure you it can<lb/> not have come at a better time.<lb/> I do not wish to make you proud<lb/> but really I must say whom a <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd"/> that I have been hearing good <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd"/>from<lb/> you of late. I was up to <placeName>Cross Roads</placeName><lb/> Sunday, (went up Saturday evening and came<lb/> down Monday morning) and while <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd">there</unclear><lb/> <persName ref="#stillja">James</persName> was telling <add place="above">me</add> how a certain judge<lb/> at whose house you stopped spoke very<lb/> highly of your intelligence and bearing <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd">and</unclear><lb/> others had observed the same. Creditable <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd">marks</unclear><lb/> of character in my niece and I also<lb/> found that our uncle <persName>Jimmy</persName> was <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd">entertaining</unclear><lb/> similar ideas of Alabamaâ€™s daughter.<lb/> Like Captain <persName>Scott</persName> when you go for<lb/> them, they come down before you shoot<lb/> as they are soon convinced that it were<lb/> folly to attempt to get away from you.
        </p>
        <p>
	        Well I have some <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd">clever agents</unclear> and the<lb/> orders are coming <add place="above">in</add> nicely. <unclear reason="faded" resp="jd">Love to P</unclear>
        </p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Your affectionate uncle</salute>
         <signed><persName ref="#stillwi"><choice><abbr>W</abbr><expan>William</expan></choice> Still</persName></signed>
        </closer>
    </body>
